import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data['budgetYear'] = data['budgetYear'].dt.year
    plt.hist(data['budgetYear'], bins=31, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['budgetYear'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['budgetYear'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of budgetYear?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['forecastYear'], bins=41, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['forecastYear'].min(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Min: {:.2f}'.format(data['forecastYear'].min()))
    plt.axvline(data['forecastYear'].max(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Max: {:.2f}'.format(data['forecastYear'].max()))
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of forecastYear?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['forecastYear'] == year]['value'] for year in data['forecastYear'].unique()])
    ax.set_xticklabels([year.year for year in data['forecastYear'].unique()])
    ax.set_xlabel('forecastYear')
    ax.set_ylabel('value')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of value for each forecastYear?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
